<br>
Problem solved.<br>
<br>
The level 52 fire pet will quad for 29 as usual and proc 140 damage based magic and fire DD's.  The level 58 and 63 fire pets will do the same.   <br>
<br>
This will give us that extra &quot;situational&quot; style pet.  Currently, the firepets are practically useless in ALL styles of combat.  They're junk.  We know that.  Verant knows that.  The ants that live in my backyard know that.  Changing the cast to proc would give us an edge against mobs like Emp or Seru as well as give the unlucky @#%$ that got the 63 firepet when they turned their scrolls in a decent pet to use.<br>
<br>
Any suggestions?<br>
<br>
What's Verant's email, btw? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moedrippins>Moe Drippins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(1/31/03 4:35:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=962.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yet Another Idea For Mage Fire Pets</span><hr size=1> I'm very low level so I'm asking because I'm curious, not because I doubt you.<br>
