<br>
Well, the 58 and 63 fire pets both cast root.  Most groups do not like rooting pets.  Why?  Well, rangers can't do their crits with bows, rogues can't evade as well, and all the melees have to watch their range on a rooted mob.  Try rooting an enraging mob as well--they flip out and start twisting around, thus ruining the idea of keeping their backs to the other melees.  The 52 fire I don't remember rooting at all, or at least not when I had him.  But the 58 and 63 definately root a LOT.  So depends on what group you're in.  Most times the same level air pet will serve you just as well as far as stunning goes, and the lack of root doesn't upset anyone.  With C2 on these pets they do seem to chain stun a lot more, thus I am convinced they base their nuking off of a mana pool.  <br>
<br>
That being said, of course this pet is useless for soloing (refer to the &quot;rooting&quot; argument).  The 63 fire pet gets &quot;shieldskin&quot; (50-ish dmg rune), &quot;shielding&quot; (50-ish dmg hp buff, ac buff, and magic resist buff... btw, wont' stack with burnout IV OR V), both utterly useless to this pet except to help him farm greenies (which he can't even do an impressive job of).  <br>
<br>
The 52 and 58 fire at least nuke for a fair amount.  They also use fire *and* magic based nukes.  The 63 fire throws out a stun that hits for a max of 70 (at least on PC's in duels), and that's it.  He doesn't cast any other sort of nuke.  For those that have him and don't believe me, test it for yourself--Child of Ro only does low low damage stun nukes and roots.  His melee is something like... 68 maybe (which isn't horrid, but much weaker than his counterparts).  Of course they cast their normal O'keil's (don't ask which one, but as if it would matter) and have next to crap for hp's.  <br>
<br>
How do I think they could be improved?  Well, this maybe have been suggested elsewhere, but having the thing do a snare instead of root (maybe single target Bonds of Force) wouldn't be horrible.  Before people start screaming about overpowering mages by giving them snare, remember that with the fire pet a majority of the damage will be coming from the mage nukes, not from the output of the pet (like other pets).  The snare could have a low duration (like BoF at 45 seconds), and the pet itself could even have it's melee dmg lowered to match the 58 fire or something.  <br>
<br>
Another suggestion is to make the 52+ fire pets akin to the Servant of Ro AA ability.  The things do such little dmg why not just have them sit back and be like real wizards?  Sony has shown they can code this by making the SoR a pure caster, so why not?  And give the Child of Ro pet something better than a 50 dmg rune and 70 dmg stun nuke.  Sure the chain stunning could be useful against casters, but it dies almost instantly on an enrage (faster than the other pets of course).  <br>
<br>
As it stands, I only pull out my fire pets as a parlor trick.  I primarily use my 61 air or 62 water for the damage/stuns, or even dabble with the epic.  Very rarely do I ever mem the Child of Ro, and the times I do I end up getting rid of him because someone in the group gets upset over the pet rooting or he ends up dying for some other reason.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
