</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=booperbustle>Booperbustle</A> at: 2/14/03 6:51:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wrathen@themagicianstower>Wrathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/03 9:44:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=962.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yet Another Idea For Mage Fire Pets</span><hr size=1> I also agree that the 52 fire pet is trash.<br>
<br>
His DPS is crap.  The nukes are ok but they don't happen enough to make any real difference for the most part.  With the air pet, you know you'll get a DD+stun every time (assuming it lands) and the water pet you know you get a cold based DD and backstabs.<br>
<br>
The 52 fire pet does root and this is absurd.  If, in a duel, you root a fire pet and back away from him, he'll randomly cast spells but at the normal rate he would cast anyways.<br>
<br>
I'd rather have a pet quadding for 54/56 than 29 when the DD spells being cast does 140s to 170s DD and the low DD+stun.<br>
<br>
Pets have never shown to have mana.  They do not benefit from the focus effects of items (yep I posted on this a while back, down to page 3 or 4 now called 'equipping pets') and seem to be on a 'random' timer on how often they can cast.<br>
<br>
As to if clarity affects them or not, there's only one way to see...logs.  But I don't think it does.<br>
<br>
I could buy the lvl 58 fire pet....but why?  It'll never be used.<br>
<br>
Wrathen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=booperbustle>Booperbustle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/03 10:59:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=962.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yet Another Idea For Mage Fire Pets</span><hr size=1> I've only really tried the clarity trick on my fire pets.  Air, Water, and Earth all tend to cast once every 6 or so seconds (you could follow a pattern of taunt, cast, taunt, cast, etc. watching the pet).  Fire pets aren't like that.  When you first bring them out, they spend a while buffing themselves, and when first attacking a mob they will seem to chain cast themselves out of mana, then melee/cast/melee/cast.  Just from testing the pet out in BoT (Child of Ro I mean), giving the pet C2 has a tremendous effect on his nuking.  Without C2 he just casts 4 or 5 times, then melees and switches back to casting every little bit.  If he has C2 he'll keep up with the casting, decreasing the time he melees in between casts, etc.  <br>
<br>
There isn't really a way to prove this using logs, save just counting how many times he casts non-cracked vs. cracked.  Anyone with the higher level fire pets test this theory and you'll see.  <br>
<br>
I will agree for a fact that the other pets don't have mana though.  They have a very distinct pattern to their nuking.  The fire is the only exception.  Regardless, he's still not a viable choice over my other pets ATM.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
